SIMPLE: intromittent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intromittent
<hw>In`tro*mit"tent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intromittens</ets>, p. pr.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Throwing, or allowing to pass, into or
within.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Used in copulation; -- said of
the external reproductive organs of the males of many animals, and
sometimes of those of the females.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intromitter</ent>⟦br⟧
